          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Promoting Good Cyber Hygiene Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill requires the National Institute of Standards and Technology to establish for the&nbsp;federal government, the private sector, and any individual or organization a list of best practices to defend against common cybersecurity threats and risks.&nbsp;</p> <p>The Department of Homeland Security must&nbsp;assess cybersecurity threats, the effect of such threats on the federal government's information systems and networks, and submit recommendations for addressing such threats. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-06-22T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
